OL,4,Cconcerns government was watering down
OL,5,Cbill
OL,7,FCampaigners argued this would allow
OL,8,Fthose running the security services to
OL,9,Fdecide whether to disclose
OL,10,Finformation, creating too broad an opt-
OL,11,Fout for authorities, leading to
OL,12,Fconcerns that the legislation was
OL,13,Fbeing watered down.
OL,15,FThe Hillsborough law, officially the
OL,16,FPublic Office (Accountability) Bill,
OL,17,Faims to force public officials and
OL,18,Fcontractors to tell the truth after
OL,19,Fdisasters.
